cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with language and semantics, specifically the detection of metaphorical senses in language over time. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses vector spaces and cosine similarity to analyze language data. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with analyzing and comparing language data over time. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques to analyze language data. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing language data using vector spaces, which can be related to neural network models.
